<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36175a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36175a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36175a"> 175(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> unproductive labour</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[The Darkness. The Criminals]</font> The cost of prosecution and maintenance of criminals, and the expense of the police involves an annual outlay of &pound;4,437,000. This, however, is small compared with the tax and toll which this predatory horde inflicts upon the community on which it is quartered. To the loss caused by the actual picking and stealing must be added that of the <mark>unproductive labour</mark> of nearly 65,000 adults. <small> William Booth, <a name="WBDE" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WBDE"><cite title="source">In Darkest England and the Way Out</cite></a> (1893) Part 1, Chapter 7</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
